theme/README.md
     1тЖТ# Theme
     3тЖТThe default renderer uses a [handlebars](https://handlebarsjs.com) template to
     4тЖТrender your markdown files and comes with a default theme included in the mdBook
     5тЖТbinary.
     6тЖТ
     7тЖТThe theme is totally customizable, you can selectively replace every file from
     8тЖТthe theme by your own by adding a `theme` directory next to `src` folder in your
     9тЖТproject root. Create a new file with the name of the file you want to override
    10тЖТand now that file will be used instead of the default file.
    11тЖТ
    12тЖТHere are the files you can override:
    13тЖТ
    14тЖТ- **_index.hbs_** is the handlebars template.
      тЖТтАж
theme/editor.md
     1тЖТ# Editor
     3тЖТIn addition to providing runnable code playgrounds, mdBook optionally allows them
     4тЖТto be editable. In order to enable editable code blocks, the following needs to
     5тЖТbe added to the ***book.toml***:
     6тЖТ
     7тЖТ```toml
     8тЖТ[output.html.playground]
     9тЖТeditable = true
    10тЖТ```
    11тЖТ
    12тЖТAfter enabling editable code blocks, the `editable` attribute must be added to a
    13тЖТcode block to make it editable:
    14тЖТ
    15тЖТ~~~markdown
    16тЖТ```rust,editable
    17тЖТfn main() {
    18тЖТ    let number = 5;
    19тЖТ    print!("{}", number);
    20тЖТ}
    21тЖТ```
    22тЖТ~~~
    23тЖТ
    24тЖТThe above will result in this editable playground:
    25тЖТ
    26тЖТ```rust,editable
    27тЖТfn main() {
    28тЖТ    let number = 5;
    29тЖТ    print!("{}", number);
    30тЖТ}
    31тЖТ```
    32тЖТ
      тЖТтАж
    35тЖТ## Customizing the editor тАж
